President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Zachary N. Somers to serve as a Judge on the United States Court of Federal Claims. Somers currently serves as the Chief Investigative Counsel for the United States Senate Committee on the Judiciary, where he handles oversight and investigations for Chairman Lindsey O. Graham. Prior to this, he served in various counsel roles for the United States House Committee on the Judiciary, including as the Committee's General Counsel and Parliamentarian. Somers also worked as an attorney at the law firm Marzulla Law, specializing in takings and breach of contract litigation before the Court of Federal Claims and other Federal courts. He holds an undergraduate degree from Georgetown University, cum laude, and a J.D. from Georgetown University Law Center, where he served as the Editor-in-Chief of the Georgetown Journal of Law & Public Policy.